+### Step 1 - Fix the architecture, bottleneck, protocol, and novelty claim
+
+- Depends on: none.
+- Action: choose exactly one inherited architecture and one mission-central bad term.
+- Action: freeze the localization protocol before comparing candidates.
+- Action: define one gain currency that every candidate will be judged in.
+- Action: state what new localized estimate or bookkeeping issue is being tested that prior project negatives did not already settle.
+- Expected output: a screening memo containing the architecture, bad term, localization protocol, gain metric, novelty claim, and a bounded candidate family.
+- Kill condition: if the chain cannot make the architecture or comparison protocol concrete, stop and write the under-specification memo.
+
